BLUETONGUE - BULGARIA: UPDATE
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Bluetongue - Bulgaria (Burgas) 990714230958
Date: Sun, 25 Jul 1999
From: *Chan Yow Cheong* <chanyowcheong@pacific.net.sg>
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for Asia
Source: O.I.E. Disease Information Periodical, 23 Jul 1999, Vol: 12
No. 28 http://www.oie.int/info/A_info.htm
Follow-up report No. 2
----------------------------
Text of a fax received on 22 July 1999 from Dr Nikola T. Belev,
Delegate of Bulgaria to the OIE:July 1999:
New outbreaks (confirmed at the laboratory) up to 19 July 1999:
Date(initial detection) -Location of clinical signs- District /Village /
Town
29 June 1999- Malko Tarnovo - Stoilovo
5 July 1999 - Malko Tarnovo - Vizitsa
5 July 1999 - Malko Tarnovo - Malko Tarnovo
7 July 1999 - Tsarevo - Balgari
7 July 1999- Tsarevo - Kondolovo
7 July 1999 - Tsarevo - Pismenovo
14 July 1999- Primorsko - Yasna Polyana
15 July 1999 - Tsarevo - Tsarevo
Total number of animals in the new outbreaks:
Species = ovine
Susceptible = 3913
Cases = 66
Deaths = 0
Destroyed = 66
Slaughtered = 0
Diagnosis: on 20 July 1999, material from sick sheep was mailed
to the OIE Reference Laboratory for bluetongue in Pirbright, United
Kingdom, for diagnosis confirmation and typing of the virus.
Control measures during reporting period: the measures mentioned
in Follow-up Report No. 1 are being maintained regarding the ban
on the movement and trade of animals, insect control on animal
premises and in forest and agricultural areas, disinfection, rodent
control and control of ectoparasites of ruminants.
........................................tg/jw
